{"title":"K-Edge MAX computer mounts get yoked for bigger GPS head unit & light combos","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/02/03/k-edge-max-computer-mounts-get-yoked-for-bigger-gps-head-unit-light-combos/","date":1612407869000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-3\"></span>When the original K-Edge computer mounts debuted, Garmins were a lot smaller. And lighter. Since then, They’ve added the Pro mounts to handle adding a light or GoPro underneath. But we kept pushing it, didn’t we?</p><p>Now, they’ve introduced the new K-Edge MAX computer mounts, designed to hold your mega GPS cycling computer and high-powered, high-lumen headlights rock steady.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-max-Combo-Mount-w-garmin-niterider-light.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-max-Combo-Mount-w-garmin-niterider-light.jpg\" alt=\"new K-Edge Max combo out front mount for cycling computers and headlights\" width=\"1200\" height=\"721\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-max-Combo-Mount-w-garmin-niterider-light.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-max-Combo-Mount-w-garmin-niterider-light.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-max-Combo-Mount-w-garmin-niterider-light-297x178.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-max-Combo-Mount-w-garmin-niterider-light-800x481.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-max-Combo-Mount-w-garmin-niterider-light-120x72.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-max-Combo-Mount-w-garmin-niterider-light-768x461.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-max-Combo-Mount-w-garmin-niterider-light-696x418.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-max-Combo-Mount-w-garmin-niterider-light-1068x642.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-max-Combo-Mount-w-garmin-niterider-light-699x420.jpg 699w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-max-Combo-Mount-w-garmin-niterider-light.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-max-Combo-Mount-w-garmin-niterider-light-297x178.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-max-Combo-Mount-w-garmin-niterider-light-800x481.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-max-Combo-Mount-w-garmin-niterider-light-120x72.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-max-Combo-Mount-w-garmin-niterider-light-768x461.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-max-Combo-Mount-w-garmin-niterider-light-696x418.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-max-Combo-Mount-w-garmin-niterider-light-1068x642.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-max-Combo-Mount-w-garmin-niterider-light-699x420.jpg 699w\"></a></p><p>Why? Because as cycling computers get bigger, they not only get heavier, but they’re also pushed farther from the bar. Which means more force cantilevered on a small piece of alloy. Add a 1200-lumen headlight or the larger new GoPro HERO9, and you could have more than half a pound sitting 3-4″ off your bar.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-3\"></span></p><p>Their payload is rated at 123g up top, and 242g below, for a total of 365g (13oz). Mounts weigh between 47g and 63g, depending on model and combo mounts, including a new version (<em>keep reading</em>).</p><p>All Pro Series Mounts (K13-1500, 1500C, 1505, 1505C, 1600C, 1605, 1605C) will be switched to the New MAX Series Mounts (K13-4500, 4500C, 4505, 4505C, 4500W, 4500WC, 4505W, 4505WC). Retail prices remain the same at $49.99 each, or $64.99 with the combo mount.</p><h3>There’s other new mounts and parts, too</h3><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-wahoo-mount-insert-in-gray.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-wahoo-mount-insert-in-gray.jpg\" alt=\"new gray insert for wahoo computers on k-edge out front mounts\" width=\"1200\" height=\"812\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-wahoo-mount-insert-in-gray.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-wahoo-mount-insert-in-gray.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-wahoo-mount-insert-in-gray-297x201.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-wahoo-mount-insert-in-gray-800x541.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-wahoo-mount-insert-in-gray-120x81.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-wahoo-mount-insert-in-gray-768x520.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-wahoo-mount-insert-in-gray-696x471.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-wahoo-mount-insert-in-gray-1068x723.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-wahoo-mount-insert-in-gray-621x420.jpg 621w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-wahoo-mount-insert-in-gray.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-wahoo-mount-insert-in-gray-297x201.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-wahoo-mount-insert-in-gray-800x541.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-wahoo-mount-insert-in-gray-120x81.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-wahoo-mount-insert-in-gray-768x520.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-wahoo-mount-insert-in-gray-696x471.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-wahoo-mount-insert-in-gray-1068x723.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/k-edge-wahoo-mount-insert-in-gray-621x420.jpg 621w\"></a></p><p>The light blue Wahoo computer mount insert will switch to gray. It’s made in Boise, ID, just like their machined alloy mounts, and will retail for $5.50 if you want to switch.</p><p><span><iframe width=\"696\" height=\"392\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/BL9BmRGve-g?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\"></iframe></span></p><p>They’ve also added a dedicated Light &amp; Motion mount that bolts to the bottom of the MAX. Check the video to see how it works!</p><p><a href=\"http://www.k-edge.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>K-edge.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"3a823d6aa404508883b215d5772716e01bc7fb6d28bae0f57b9b772a6ac4c1cd","category":"Cycling"}